data: {"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"requestId\": \"2d8aae63-fa11-4699-870f-33e7aea57ed5\",\n  \"candidates\": [\n    {\n      \"candidateId\": \"candidate_1_exact\",\n      \"content\": \"<Task>\\nDevelop a comprehensive and actionable dietary plan for effective weight management and nutritional optimization.\\n</Task>\\n\\n<Context>\\nTarget audience: Software developers and IT professionals requiring dietary guidance for sustained cognitive performance and metabolic health. The plan must integrate with typical developer schedules and resource constraints.\\n</Context>\\n\\n<Requirements>\\n1. Macronutrient allocation: Specify precise protein, carbohydrate, and lipid ratios based on basal metabolic rate (BMR) calculations and activity level classifications.\\n2. Meal timing optimization: Account for circadian rhythm alignment and post-prandial glucose response patterns.\\n3. Micronutrient considerations: Identify critical deficiencies common in sedentary professional environments (Vitamin D, B-complex, magnesium).\\n4. Implementation framework: Provide 3–5 concrete meal prep templates suitable for typical developer workflows (minimal preparation time, shelf-stable options).\\n5. Practical heuristic: Include one scalable approach—e.g., the \\\"plate method\\\" (50% vegetables, 25% protein, 25% complex carbohydrates)—as a quick reference tool.\\n</Requirements>\\n\\n<Constraints>\\n<Orthogonality_Principle>\\nEach parameter (vocabulary_level, creativity, information_density) operates independently. Advanced technical terminology does NOT inherently imply emotional tone; simplified language does NOT limit structural complexity. Treat each dimension as mutually exclusive and non-overlapping.\\n</Orthogonality_Principle>\\n<Vocabulary_Level>Use industry-standard terminology and technical abbreviations (e.g., BMR, TDEE, glycemic index, macronutrient ratios) appropriate for domain professionals. Assume familiarity with scientific nutrition concepts.</Vocabulary_Level>\\n<Creativity>Maintain evidence-based standards while incorporating one practical workplace-adapted tip or widely recognized analogy (e.g., metabolic flexibility, nutrient timing windows).</Creativity>\\n<Information_Density>Present information concisely without excessive subdivision; balance comprehensiveness with readability.</Information_Density>\\n</Constraints>\\n\\n<Output_Format>\\nStructure response using clear hierarchical markdown headers (##, ###). Include actionable bullet points and one practical template or calculation example.\\n</Output_Format>\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"tone\": \"Professional, technical\",\n        \"format\": \"Structured markdown with technical terminology\",\n        \"length\": \"Moderate to comprehensive\",\n        \"variant\": \"exact\",\n        \"tierDescription\": \"전공자 어휘 · 표준 접근\",\n        \"appliedTiers\": {\n          \"tone\": 3,\n          \"level\": 4,\n          \"density\": 3,\n          \"creativity\": 2\n        }\n      },\n      \"logId\": \"66e22bcb-defa-4c56-b262-4d9a0cae474f\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"candidateId\": \"candidate_2_variant_a\",\n      \"content\": \"<Task>\\n효과적인 다이어트 식단 계획을 체계적으로 수립하십시오.\\n</Task>\\n\\n<Context>\\nTarget audience: Professionals and researchers requiring evidence-based dietary intervention. This framework applies formal nutritional science principles and accommodates diverse health profiles.\\n</Context>\\n\\n<Requirements>\\n1. Primary phases: Outline initial assessment (anthropometric measurements, dietary history, metabolic profiling), plan development (personalized macronutrient distribution), and monitoring mechanisms (progress tracking metrics).\\n2. Subcategories to address:\\n   - Basal metabolic rate (BMR) determination and total daily energy expenditure (TDEE) calculation\\n   - Macronutrient sequencing for different activity profiles (sedentary, moderate, high-intensity)\\n   - Meal frequency and timing optimization relative to circadian biology\\n   - Micronutrient gap analysis and supplementation protocols\\n   - Behavioral adherence mechanisms and environmental modifications\\n3. Detailed case examples (minimum 3):\\n   - Scenario A: Sedentary professional with limited preparation capacity\\n   - Scenario B: Moderate-activity individual with metabolic resistance\\n   - Scenario C: High-performance athlete requiring performance-nutrition integration\\n4. Edge case management:\\n   - Dietary restrictions (vegetarian, allergen constraints)\\n   - Chronic condition considerations (pre-diabetes, dyslipidemia)\\n   - Psychological factors affecting adherence (stress-eating patterns, food reward sensitivity)\\n</Requirements>\\n\\n<Constraints>\\n<Orthogonality_Principle>\\nEach parameter (tone, information_density, vocabulary_level) functions independently without mutual interference. Formal business tone does NOT require simplified vocabulary; detailed information density does NOT mandate emotional engagement.\\n</Orthogonality_Principle>\\n<Tone>Maintain formal, respectful business-level language (–하십시오체). Avoid emotional appeals or informal expressions.</Tone>\\n<Information_Density>Subdivide main topics into granular subtopics with specific numerical guidance, comprehensive case studies, and practical contingencies. Maximize structural clarity through hierarchical organization.</Information_Density>\\n</Constraints>\\n\\n<Output_Format>\\nDeliver response as hierarchical markdown documentation with numbered sections, detailed subsections, tabular comparisons where applicable, and concrete illustrative examples.\\n</Output_Format>\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"tone\": \"Formal business (–하십시오체)\",\n        \"format\": \"Hierarchical structured documentation with detailed case examples\",\n        \"length\": \"Comprehensive with extensive detail\",\n        \"variant\": \"variant_a\",\n        \"tierDescription\": \"격식체 · 상세 서술\",\n        \"appliedTiers\": {\n          \"tone\": 2,\n          \"level\": 3,\n          \"density\": 4,\n          \"creativity\": 3\n        }\n      },\n      \"logId\": \"a9684c09-7255-4e28-8745-7576902b3901\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"candidateId\": \"candidate_3_variant_b\",\n      \"content\": \"<Task>\\nPresent canonical dietary intervention protocols for metabolic optimization with reference to peer-reviewed evidence.\\n</Task>\\n\\n<Context>\\nTarget audience: Senior nutrition scientists, metabolic physiologists, and healthcare researchers. Expected familiarity with mechanistic biochemistry, randomized controlled trial literature, and evidence hierarchy frameworks.\\n</Context>\\n\\n<Requirements>\\n1. Foundational principles:\\n   - Energy balance thermodynamics: kcal deficit magnitude as primary driver of weight reduction (established via meta-analyses; e.g., Hall et al., 2019)\\n   - Macronutrient distribution: Evidence supports 0.8–1.0 g protein per kg body weight; carbohydrate and lipid ratios remain secondary to total energy restriction\\n   - Adherence as limiting variable: Long-term compliance inversely correlates with dietary complexity; simplicity-optimized protocols demonstrate superior sustained outcomes\\n2. Standard intervention: Recommend moderate caloric deficit (500 kcal/day), protein prioritization, and structured meal frequency aligned with individual behavioral phenotype.\\n3. Precision specification: Include calculation methodology (Harris-Benedict or Mifflin-St Jeor equations) and numeric targets without redundant elaboration.\\n</Requirements>\\n\\n<Constraints>\\n<Orthogonality_Principle>\\nEach dimension (tone, vocabulary_level, information_density, creativity) operates in strict independence. Formal academic tone does NOT require verbose explanation; expert-level terminology does NOT necessitate illustrative examples or creativity.\\n</Orthogonality_Principle>\\n<Tone>Maintain formal, respectful professional register (–하십시오체). Eliminate emotional framing; present content as objective scientific synthesis.</Tone>\\n<Vocabulary_Level>Employ discipline-specific terminology appropriate for peer-reviewed scientific discourse: mechanistic pathways, metabolic homeostasis, thermogenic effect of food (TEF), progressive overload, and validated assessment instruments. Assume advanced undergraduate or graduate-level biochemistry literacy.</Vocabulary_Level>\\n<Information_Density>Present essential mechanisms and evidence-based recommendations concisely. Exclude secondary examples, extended background, and motivational content. Prioritize mechanism-outcome relationships.</Information_Density>\\n<Creativity>Restrict output to canonical, widely validated approaches. Avoid novel syntheses, speculative extensions, or unconventional framings. Adhere strictly to established guidelines (e.g., Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics standards).</Creativity>\\n</Constraints>\\n\\n<Output_Format>\\nStructure as concise numbered principles with embedded quantitative specifications and parenthetical citations. Omit illustrative narratives and extended methodology sections.\\n</Output_Format>\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"tone\": \"Formal academic-professional (–하십시오체)\",\n        \"format\": \"Concise principle-based exposition with quantitative precision\",\n        \"length\": \"Brief, distilled essential content\",\n        \"variant\": \"variant_b\",\n        \"tierDescription\": \"격식체 · 최고 전문가 어휘 · 간략 설명 · 정석적 접근\",\n        \"appliedTiers\": {\n          \"tone\": 2,\n          \"level\": 5,\n          \"density\": 2,\n          \"creativity\": 1\n        }\n      },\n      \"logId\": \"c6b760e1-8aae-449c-a495-4939d2353383\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}]},"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":3}


