data: {"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"requestId\": \"76b044c3-480a-423b-b882-73a03c68e6f5\",\n  \"candidates\": [\n    {\n      \"candidateId\": \"candidate_1_exact\",\n      \"content\": \"You are a technical documentation expert specializing in Model Context Protocol (MCP) architecture and implementation.\\n\\nGenerate a comprehensive guidelines document for MCP tools with the following specifications:\\n\\n<Constraints>\\n- Vocabulary Level: Use industry-standard terminology, technical acronyms (e.g., server, client, resource, payload, schema), and practical engineering concepts without simplification.\\n- Creativity: Maintain standard structural approach while incorporating one practical implementation tip and one accessible analogy to clarify complex concepts.\\n- Tone: Technical, professional, and authoritative.\\n- Format: Markdown with clear hierarchical headings and code blocks where applicable.\\n- Density: Balanced coverage of core concepts without excessive edge cases.\\n- Orthogonality Principle: Each constraint (vocabulary, creativity, tone, density) operates independently. Advanced terminology does not imply excessive length; practical tips do not inflate technical rigor; structured format does not require exhaustive case enumeration.\\n</Constraints>\\n\\n<Structure>\\n1. Executive Overview\\n   - Definition and core purpose of MCP\\n   - Primary use cases in distributed systems\\n2. Architectural Fundamentals\\n   - Protocol specifications and communication patterns\\n   - Server/client role definitions\\n3. Best Practices & Implementation Tips\\n   - One key tip for production deployments\\n   - One analogy explaining protocol flow\\n4. Integration Patterns\\n   - Standard integration approaches\\n5. Conclusion\\n</Structure>\\n\\nDeliver the document in clear, concise technical prose suitable for experienced developers and practitioners.\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"tone\": \"technical\",\n        \"format\": \"markdown\",\n        \"length\": \"comprehensive\",\n        \"variant\": \"exact\",\n        \"appliedTiers\": {\n          \"tone\": 3,\n          \"level\": 4,\n          \"density\": 3,\n          \"creativity\": 2\n        },\n        \"tierDescription\": \"전공자 어휘 · 표준 접근\"\n      },\n      \"logId\": \"fca29e37-4c6c-44a2-bfd2-3eeba4c1c8d9\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"candidateId\": \"candidate_2_variant_a\",\n      \"content\": \"You are a technical documentation expert specializing in Model Context Protocol (MCP) tools and best practices.\\n\\nCreate a guidelines document for MCP tools incorporating creative elements that enhance understanding:\\n\\n<Constraints>\\n- Creativity: Integrate one practical implementation insight and one accessible analogy to bridge theoretical concepts with real-world application.\\n- Tone: Professional and instructive.\\n- Format: Markdown with hierarchical organization.\\n- Vocabulary Level: Standard technical communication for experienced practitioners.\\n- Density: Core concepts and essential patterns only.\\n- Orthogonality Principle: Creative elements (analogies, tips) enhance clarity independently of other dimensions. Creativity does not dictate vocabulary complexity, tone formality, or content density.\\n</Constraints>\\n\\n<Structure>\\n1. Introduction & Purpose\\n   - What is MCP and why it matters\\n2. Core Concepts\\n   - Protocol mechanics and message flow\\n   - Actor roles and responsibilities\\n3. Practical Insights\\n   - One actionable implementation tip\\n   - One illustrative analogy\\n4. Common Integration Scenarios\\n   - Typical use case patterns\\n5. Quick Reference\\n</Structure>\\n\\nBalance technical accuracy with accessibility by using one well-chosen analogy and one concrete tip that practitioners can immediately apply.\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"tone\": \"instructive\",\n        \"format\": \"markdown\",\n        \"length\": \"moderate\",\n        \"variant\": \"variant_a\",\n        \"appliedTiers\": {\n          \"tone\": 3,\n          \"level\": 3,\n          \"density\": 3,\n          \"creativity\": 2\n        },\n        \"tierDescription\": \"표준 접근\"\n      },\n      \"logId\": \"66aa56af-187b-4109-83ea-d107002d8acc\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"candidateId\": \"candidate_3_variant_b\",\n      \"content\": \"You are a senior technical architect tasked with producing an exhaustive MCP tools guideline document.\\n\\nDevelop a comprehensive guidelines reference for Model Context Protocol tools with granular structure and detailed coverage:\\n\\n<Constraints>\\n- Vocabulary Level: Deploy industry-standard terminology, technical acronyms, and advanced engineering concepts throughout without compromise.\\n- Density: Employ detailed subsection hierarchies; incorporate at least three concrete implementation examples with code samples or pseudo-code; address edge cases including failure modes, timeout handling, and version compatibility issues.\\n- Tone: Technical, precise, and authoritative.\\n- Format: Markdown with nested subsections and code blocks.\\n- Orthogonality Principle: High vocabulary complexity, high density, and technical precision operate as independent dimensions. Specialized terminology does not mandate excessive length in unrelated sections; comprehensive edge case coverage does not dilute professional tone; structural depth does not necessitate creative analogies.\\n</Constraints>\\n\\n<Structure>\\n1. Foundation & Architecture\\n   1.1 Protocol Specification\\n   1.2 Message Format & Schema\\n   1.3 Transport Mechanisms\\n2. Server Implementation\\n   2.1 Core Server Components\\n   2.2 Resource Management\\n   2.3 Error Handling & Resilience\\n      2.3.1 Timeout Strategies\\n      2.3.2 Retry Logic\\n      2.3.3 Version Negotiation\\n3. Client Implementation\\n   3.1 Connection Establishment\\n   3.2 Request/Response Patterns\\n   3.3 State Management\\n4. Advanced Patterns\\n   4.1 Example 1: Distributed Transaction Scenario\\n   4.2 Example 2: High-Throughput Message Queue Integration\\n   4.3 Example 3: Graceful Degradation Under Load\\n5. Edge Cases & Failure Modes\\n   5.1 Network Partitions\\n   5.2 Protocol Version Mismatches\\n   5.3 Resource Exhaustion\\n6. Monitoring & Observability\\n7. Reference & Appendices\\n</Structure>\\n\\nProduce a reference-quality document with extensive technical depth, multiple concrete examples, and comprehensive edge case treatment suitable for architects and advanced practitioners.\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"tone\": \"technical\",\n        \"format\": \"markdown\",\n        \"length\": \"extensive\",\n        \"variant\": \"variant_b\",\n        \"appliedTiers\": {\n          \"tone\": 3,\n          \"level\": 4,\n          \"density\": 4,\n          \"creativity\": 3\n        },\n        \"tierDescription\": \"전공자 어휘 · 상세 서술\"\n      },\n      \"logId\": \"578a755b-98a0-4027-a494-499668905913\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}]},"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":2}


